author: Cleo Abram
description:
Alarms start blaring when a plane goes into zero gravity! On a Zero G flight, one pilot’s job is to figure out which alarms matter and turn off the others. One that gets turned off every time? The low fuel warning.

Because everyone on this plane starts experiencing zero gravity… so does the fuel. It floats away from the fuel pumps which means soon it won’t be getting to the engines. 

But that’s ok because…

#shorts #ZeroG #Airplane #Technology #Science
title: This Airplane Fuel Is Floating. Uh Oh.
